er &quot;Yes I think you are. Close your eyes and seek the Plane of Earth. Good. Good. Now turn to the heat feel it? ........ Good now go towards it. Not to close mind you, for you are not of the Academy. Now feel for them do you feel them?&quot; *Deep in the Plane of Earth. My mind spread thin across the plane one with the plane. I feel the strength and heat from the area my mind is concentrated. I feel the shifting of the earth around me and I spin tread after thread out linking the area to the others I am linked with and to my mind. * The Master &quot;Yes that is it. We are very proud. You have gone very deep for you first time to this area now pull back. That right, very good. No you have access to the next form of Earth Element. Keep this up and soon you will be summon the final level. * The master smiles* &quot;Now go. Defend our realm Young Defender.&quot; <br>
<br>
*Beaming with pride I walk out before the door even closes I am running down the hall and across the road into the woods looking for something to try my new Elemental on. I see a short distance away a Zombie shambling along thru the bushes. I reach within my self, making the gesters and say the words of power. The earth weals up before me. The heat of my love for the land and my hate for those that would hurt those that live there helping fuel the internal fires of the new Elemental. The body the gray black of new Lava. Thru the cracks of it new harder stronger skill can be seen the lava that makes it blood flowing thru it. With a nod it turns and runs off into the bushes* What? ~Did it just nod to me? No it could not have nodded! ~ *A single sound like a rotten melon hitting the ground is heard then silence. I wait to hear the sounds of battle and there is nothing. I slowly move up around the bush to see my Lava Elemental standing over the mashed form of what can only be the Zombie. A Goblin stands open-mouthed looking at the pile with a small wisp of smoke rising from it. I quickly again summon another Laval Elemental sending it against the Goblin as the first elemental Gives a cry of pain? Loneliness’? * ~Could it be? Are they really intelligent? No it is not possible. I will not go down the same path as them I will not go mad! ~ *The Laval Elemental runs up on the goblin taking a swing exploding it's head as with the sound of a rotten gourd being struck, and it looks that way too. The neck smoldering with the heat that comes from the fist of the Laval Elemental. I turn and run before the Elemental could give its cry. <br>
<br>
